 to\ntry to keep atomic knowledge from\nthe world \u201cfor any appreciable\ntime.\u201d\nTestifying before a Joint senate\nsubcommittee in favor of legislation\nto provide government support for\na .entitle research. Shapley said\natomic energy can be of value to\nthe whole world.\n\u201cScientists.\" he declared, \u201caw\nworld cltls*ns serving all mankind\nIf they are to help make the world\nsafe for civilization, they must work\nfor a future in which narrowly na\ntional Interests diminish and world\nwide responsibilities Increase.\u201d\n8\u00ablon^ Btyicn'\nMeanwhile the louse Military Af\nfairs Committee began bearings or\nlegislation requested by Prestden\nTruman to establish a commlsstor\nto supervise the development am\ncontrol of atomic power.\nCommittee chairman Andrew J\nlfically\naccordance with\nquest.\u201d The measure\npresidential appointment,\nsenate approval, of a\natomic energy comm\ncomplete control within\nof atomic energy\nuse.\nIn the senate\nwas bogged down in a\nto which committee\nwhich\nsidering\nbut the who)\nresearch in\nto advance\nThe bill\nestablish a\nfor adentif","height":"28332","width":"20828"}}
